      "id": 35156,
      "name": "JenMDX",
      "username": "JenMDX",
      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/a5b964/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2023-10-19T19:56:26.419Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Hi,</p>\n<p>I did the first workout in the Spartan Base - Minimalist training plan - recovery 45/60 today but I was finding it hard to keep my watts down low enough to fit the criteria.</p>\n<p>I have a spin bike but it doesn\u2019t have auto resistance so I was having to pedal slower than what is natural or increase the resistance to reduce cadence but I didn\u2019t want to push my heart rate up too high and on most bikes with auto resistance that would push the wattage up?</p>\n<p>I did a ramp test and in theory my FTP is about 100 which is what I set the workout too after importing into Zwift but I\u2019m wondering how I\u2019m supposed to tackle this workout?</p>\n<p>It was 45watts and 60 watts but though 60 was okay I was mostly doing 50-55 watts during the 7min 45 watts sections.</p>\n<p>Should I just try to pedal very slowly or should I increase the FTP?</p>\n<p>I\u2019m not sure what I am aiming for as a beginner to the workouts.</p>",
